Also this new version of the script is resulting in 40 extra bodies of output after running and they look like the intersection regions before splitting. There's a copy bodies operation happening somewhere that is running at the wrong time, or running a second time unnecessarily. For context on how subtract complement works, it's essentially an intersection boolean except that it is identity preserving and modifies the bodies in the targets step instead of generating new ones. Additionally, and unlike boolean intersect which delivers only the middle venn diagram common to all inputs, subtract complement operations will deliver the commonalities between the two input groups, but preserving the identity of the primary bodies in the one group. This lets me shove a bunch of stuff into group A and group B and do a multi intersection without doing it iteratively and more expensively. The copy operation for the tool bodies before the subtract complement is to not throw away the original B set of bodies which otherwise get consumed by a subtract complement operation.

